<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Seadus reguleerib raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamisel, reisijate ja kaupade veol ning riikliku j&auml;relevalvega seonduvaid toiminguid raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act regulates the rights and obligations of railway undertakings in the management of railway infrastructure and in transport of passengers and goods, and acts related to state supervision of railway undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Seadus kehtestab avalik-&otilde;iguslikud kitsendused raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate tegevusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act establishes restrictions in public law on the activities of railway undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee, raudteeinfrastruktuur ja raudteemaa </eesti>
<inglise>Railway, railway infrastructure and railway ground area </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudtee on maat&uuml;kiga p&uuml;sivalt &uuml;hendatud rajatis, mille olulisteks osadeks on muldkeha ja sellele toetuv tee pealisehitus, mis koosneb r&ouml;&ouml;bastest, p&ouml;&ouml;rangutest, liipritest ja ballastist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) "Railway" means a construction which is permanently attached to a plot of land and the essential parts of which are the track bed and the superstructure which consists of rails, switch blades, sleepers and ballast and is supported by the track bed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeinfrastruktuur on raudtee ning raudtee majandamiseks vajalikud hooned ja rajatised. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) "Railway infrastructure" means railways, and buildings and constructions necessary for the management of railways. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri hooned on raudteemaal asuvad hooned, milles paiknevad raudteeveoks vajalikud m&uuml;&uuml;gi- ja teenindusvahendid v&otilde;i mida muul viisil kasutatakse raudtee sihtotstarbeliseks kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) "Railway infrastructure buildings" mean buildings which are located in railway ground areas and contain sales and service facilities necessary for rail transport, or which are utilised for the use of railways for their intended purposes in any other manner. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri rajatised on: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) "Railway infrastructure constructions" mean: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sillad, viaduktid, estakaadid, tunnelid, tugiseinad, truubid, s&uuml;vendid, rennid ja kraavid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) bridges, viaducts, trestles, tunnels, retaining walls, culverts, cuttings, channels and ditches; </inglise>
<eesti>2) turvangu-, side-, valgustus- ja energiaseadmed ning tehnorajatised; </eesti>
<inglise>2) safety equipment, communication equipment, lighting installations, energy equipment and engineering constructions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;lek&auml;igu- ja &uuml;les&otilde;idukohad; </eesti>
<inglise>3) crossings; 4) access routes to railways; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juurdep&auml;&auml;suteed raudteele; 5) jaamad ja teised meldepunktid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) stations and other safety signalling and telecommunication installation points on tracks; </inglise>
<eesti>6) reisi- ja kaubaplatvormid; </eesti>
<inglise>6) passenger and goods platforms; </inglise>
<eesti>7) teekaitseobjektid; </eesti>
<inglise>7) track protection structures; </inglise>
<eesti>8) muud raudtee sihtotstarbeliseks kasutamiseks vajalikud rajatised. </eesti>
<inglise>8) other constructions necessary for the use of railways for their intended purposes. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Raudteemaa on raudtee ja raudtee sihtotstarbeliseks kasutamiseks vajalike hoonete ja rajatiste alune ning nende teenindamiseks vajalik maa. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) "Railway ground area" means the land under a railway, and under buildings and constructions necessary for the use of the railway for its intended purpose, and the land necessary for servicing the railway, buildings and constructions. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Raudteed, mis on vajalikud sisse- ja v&auml;ljas&otilde;iduks depoosse v&otilde;i tehnohoolduspunkti v&otilde;i s&otilde;iduks depoos v&otilde;i on &uuml;ksnes vedu toetava v&otilde;i abistava iseloomuga (depooteed), ei kuulu raudteeinfrastruktuuri hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Railway infrastructure does not include railways which are necessary for entry into or departure from depots or railway repair workshops, or for movement within depots, or railways which only support transport (depot sidings). </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Rippraudtee, trammitee ja nendega ehitus- v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;viisi poolest sarnane tee v&otilde;i muu raudteest erinevat ehituslikku laadi r&ouml;&ouml;bastee ei ole raudtee k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) For the purposes of this Act, suspension railways, tramways and roads similar thereto in their manner of construction or operation, and other rail tracks the construction of which is different from railways are not deemed to be railways. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad </eesti>
<inglise>Railway undertakings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on &auml;riregistrisse kantud f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hing, kelle tegevuseks on raudteeveoteenuse osutamine v&otilde;i raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, "railway undertaking" means a sole proprietor or company which is entered in the commercial register and the area of activity of which is the provision of rail transport services or the management of railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja, kes osutab raudteeveoteenust, on k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, "rail transport undertaking" means a railway undertaking who provides rail transport services. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja, kes majandab raudteeinfrastruktuuri, on k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjaks. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, "railway infrastructure manager" means a railway undertaking which manages railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjale, kes osutab raudteeveoteenust ja majandab raudteeinfrastruktuuri, kohaldatakse raudteeveoteenuse osutamisel k&auml;esolevas seaduses raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja ja raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamisel raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja kohta s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Railway undertakings which provide rail transport services and manage railway infrastructure shall, in the provision of rail transport services, be governed by the provisions of this Act concerning rail transport undertakings and, in the management of railway infrastructure, by the provisions of this Act concerning railway infrastructure managers. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja majandab avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteeinfrastruktuuri ja kasutab seda avaliku raudteeveoteenuse osutamiseks, peab ta t&auml;itma k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 26 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>If a railway undertaking manages railway infrastructure designated for public use and uses such infrastructure for the provision of public rail transport services, the railway undertaking shall comply with the requirements specified in subsection 26 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjaks ei loeta ettev&otilde;tjat, kelle tegevuseks on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 2 l&otilde;igetes 6 ja 7 nimetatud teede majandamine v&otilde;i sellistel teedel veoteenuse osutamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Undertakings whose area of activity is the management of the rail tracks specified in subsections 2 (6) or (7) of this Act, or the provision of transport services on such rail tracks are not deemed to be railway undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamine </eesti>
<inglise>Management of railway infrastructure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamine on raudteeinfrastruktuuri korrashoid, raudteeliikluse korraldamine ning raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutada andmine raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) "Management of railway infrastructure" means the maintenance of railway infrastructure, the organisation of railway traffic and the grant of the use of railway infrastructure to railway undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri korrashoid k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on selle ehitamine ja rajamine, remont ja hooldamine. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, "maintenance of railway infrastructure" means the building, construction, repair and maintenance of railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamise v&otilde;ib raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja anda lepingu alusel &uuml;le teisele ettev&otilde;tjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A railway infrastructure manager may transfer the management of a railway infrastructure to another undertaking on the basis of an agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>Sel juhul j&auml;&auml;b ta vastutama raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamisest tulenevate kohustuste rikkumise eest solidaarselt ettev&otilde;tjaga, kellele ta raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamise &uuml;le andis. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the railway infrastructure manager and the undertaking to which the management of the railway infrastructure is transferred shall be solidarily liable for violation of the obligations arising from the management of the railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellega vastuolus olev kokkulepe on kolmandate isikute suhtes t&uuml;hine. </eesti>
<inglise>Any agreement contrary to the specified requirement is void with regard to third persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee raudteeinfrastruktuuri v&otilde;ib raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;&otilde;randada v&otilde;i selle alust maad hoonestus&otilde;igusega koormata Raudteeameti eelneval n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A railway infrastructure manager may transfer the railway infrastructure of a railway designated for public use or encumber the land under such infrastructure with a right of superficies with the prior consent of the Railway Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteevedu ja raudteeveerem </eesti>
<inglise>Rail transport and rail vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteevedu on reisijate v&otilde;i kaupade vedamine raudteel rongi v&otilde;i r&ouml;&ouml;basbussiga raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutades. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) "Rail transport" means the transport of passengers or goods on railway by train or rail bus, using railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeveerem on raudteeveoks vajalikud vedurid, vagunid, samuti dresiinid, teeremondimasinad ja muud raudteel liiklemiseks vajalikud masinad ja mehhanismid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) "Rail vehicle" means a locomotive or carriage necessary for rail transport, and a trolley, road repair machine and other machinery necessary for rail traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of railway infrastructure </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja, kes majandab avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteed, korraldab raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamist raudtee l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamise teel, eraldades raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud alusel ja korras l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosasid, sealhulgas rongiliinina v&otilde;i muul viisil. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A railway infrastructure manager who manages a railway designated for public use shall organise the use of railway infrastructure by distribution of railway capacity, allocating railway capacity to rail transport undertakings as train paths or in any other manner on the basis of and pursuant to the procedure prescribed by this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rongiliin on raudtee l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa, mis on vajalik &uuml;he rongi k&auml;igushoidmiseks siht- ja saatepunkti vahel teatud ajavahemikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) "Train path" means the railway capacity necessary for the operation of a train from the point of origin to the point of destination during a given period of time. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee ja avalik raudteeveoteenus </eesti>
<inglise>Railways designated for public use and public rail transport services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras m&auml;&auml;rab teede- ja sideminister raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel tema majandamisel oleva raudtee avalikuks kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic, the Minister of Transport and Communications shall designate a railway for public use at the request of the railway undertaking which manages the railway. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee on raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja raudteeinfrastruktuur, mille kasutamine on tasu, aja ja muude kasutamistingimuste osas diskrimineerimata tagatud k&otilde;igile raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjatele avaliku raudteeveoteenuse osutamiseks k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) "Railway designated for public use" means the railway infrastructure of a railway undertaking the use of which is ensured without discrimination with regard to fees, time or other conditions of use to all railway undertakings for the provision of public rail transport services on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras m&auml;&auml;rab teede- ja sideminister raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel tema kuulumise avalikku raudteeveoteenust osutavate raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate hulka. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic, the Minister of Transport and Communications shall, at the request of a railway undertaking, designate the railway undertaking as a railway undertaking providing public rail transport services. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja, kes on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 3 kohaselt m&auml;&auml;ratud avalikku raudteeveoteenust osutama, on vastavalt teenuse sihtotstarbele ja avalikustatud veoeeskirjadele seaduses s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras kohustatud osutama avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteel reisijate- v&otilde;i kaubaveoteenust iga&uuml;hele (avalik raudteeveoteenus). </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Railway undertakings which in accordance with subsection (3) of this section are designated to provide public rail transport services are required to provide to everyone with transport services for passengers and goods on railways designated for public use in accordance with the intended purpose of services and the published transport rules, and on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided by law (public rail transport services). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteede loetelu ja selle muudatused ning avalikku raudteeveoteenust osutavate raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate loetelu ja selle muudatused avaldatakse teadaandena Riigi Teataja Lisas. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The list of railways designated for public use, the list of railway undertakings providing public rail transport services, and amendments to such lists shall be published as notices in the Riigi Teataja Lisa (2). </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandava v&otilde;i avalikku raudteeveoteenust osutava &auml;ri&uuml;hingu &uuml;hinemine ja jagunemine on lubatud vaid Raudteeameti eelneval n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The merger and division of a company which manages the infrastructure of a railway designated for public use or provides public rail transport services is permitted only with the prior consent of the Railway Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Vabariigi Valitsusel on &otilde;igus iseseisvalt m&auml;&auml;rata raudtee avalikuks kasutamiseks &otilde;iglase tasu eest, kui raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamine on vajalik &uuml;ldistes huvides &uuml;hiskondliku veoteenuse osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Government of the Republic has the right to independently designate a railway for public use for a fair charge if the use of the railway infrastructure is necessary for the provision of public utility transport services in the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusload </eesti>
<inglise>Operating Licences </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba </eesti>
<inglise>Activity licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee raudteeinfrastruktuuri v&otilde;ib majandada raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja, kellele Raudteeamet on selleks andnud raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamise tegevusloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A railway undertaking to which the Railway Administration has issued an operating licence for the management of railway infrastructure may manage the infrastructure of a railway designated for public use. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudtee reisijateveoteenust v&otilde;ib osutada raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja, kellele Raudteeamet on selleks andnud raudtee reisijateveoteenuse tegevusloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A rail transport undertaking to which the Railway Administration has issued an operating licence for the provision of rail transport services for passengers may provide rail transport services for passengers. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteel v&otilde;ib raudtee kaubaveoteenust osutada raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja, kellele Raudteeamet on selleks andnud raudtee kaubaveoteenuse tegevusloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A rail transport undertaking to which the Railway Administration has issued an operating licence for the provision of rail transport services for goods may provide rail transport services for goods on railways designated for public use. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee ja teiste raudteeinfrastruktuuri rajatiste ehitust&ouml;id v&otilde;ib teostada ettev&otilde;tja, kellele Raudteeamet on selleks andnud raudtee-ehitustegevuse tegevusloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An undertaking to which the Railway Administration has issued an operating licence for the performance of construction work on railways may perform construction work on railways designated for public use and on other railway infrastructure constructions. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteel kasutatavat raudteeveeremit v&otilde;ib remontida ettev&otilde;tja, kellele Raudteeamet on selleks andnud raudteeveeremi remondi tegevusloa. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An undertaking to which the Railway Administration has issued an operating licence for rail vehicle repair may repair the rail vehicles used on railways designated for public use. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Tegevusluba antakse t&auml;htaega m&auml;&auml;ramata. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Operating licences shall be issued for an unspecified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Tegevusluba ei ole &uuml;leantav ning selle &uuml;leandmine teisele isikule ja kasutamine teise isiku poolt on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Operating licences are not transferable, and the transfer of an operating licence to another person or the use thereof by other persons is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) V&auml;lisriigi &auml;ri&uuml;hing v&otilde;ib tegutseda k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-5 nimetatud tegevusaladel vaid juhul, kui tema filiaal on kantud &auml;riregistrisse &auml;riseadustikus (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360) etten&auml;htud tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A foreign company may operate in the areas of activity specified in subsections (1) - (5) of this section only if a branch of the company is entered in the commercial register under the conditions prescribed in the Commercial Code (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; RT I 1998, 91/93, 1500; 1999, 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 10, 155; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185). </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Tegevusluba ei ole vajalik v&auml;lisriigi raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjale raudtee piirijaamadesse sisenemiseks, kui rahvusvahelise kokkuleppe alusel on v&auml;lisriigi raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja ja Eesti raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja piire &uuml;letava raudteeveoteenuse osutamises kokku leppinud. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) A foreign railway undertaking need not hold an operating licence in order to enter railway frontier stations if the foreign railway undertaking and an Estonian railway undertaking have, on the basis of an international agreement, agreed to provide cross-border rail transport services. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusluba ei ole vajalik v&auml;lisriigi raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjale ja nende &uuml;hendustele, kui selles on vastastikku kokku lepitud rahvusvaheliste kokkulepetega. </eesti>
<inglise>Foreign railway undertakings or associations thereof need not hold operating licences if this is mutually agreed upon in international agreements. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa andmise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions on issue of operating licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ettev&otilde;tjale antakse tegevusluba, kui ettev&otilde;tja vastab k&otilde;igile j&auml;rgmistele tingimustele: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operating licence shall be issued to an undertaking which complies with all the following requirements: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tja ja tema esitatud dokumendid vastavad seadustes ja teistes &otilde;igusaktides kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the undertaking and the documents submitted by the undertaking comply with the requirements established by law and other legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhatuse liikmed v&otilde;i teised juhtima &otilde;igustatud isikud on piisavalt usaldusv&auml;&auml;rsed, neile ei ole v&auml;lja kuulutatud pankrotti, neid ei ole s&uuml;&uuml;di m&otilde;istetud majandus- ja ametialaste kuritegude eest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the sole proprietor, the members of the management board of the company, or other persons with management rights are sufficiently reliable, they have not been declared bankrupt, have not been convicted of economic criminal offences or criminal official misconduct; </inglise>
<eesti>3) f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tjal v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu juhatuse liikmel v&otilde;i teistel juhtima &otilde;igustatud isikutel on piisavaid erialaseid teadmisi v&otilde;i kogemusi, tagamaks raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja ohutu tegevuse, selle usaldusv&auml;&auml;rse korralduse ja kontrolli; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the sole proprietor, the members of the management board of the company, or other persons with management rights have sufficient professional knowledge or experience to ensure the safe operation, reliable organisation and control of the railway undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ettev&otilde;tja raudteeohutuse ja raudteeliikluse juhtimise eest vastutavad t&ouml;&ouml;tajad on vajaliku kvalifikatsiooniga ning suudavad tagada osutatavate teenuste ohutuse n&otilde;utaval tasemel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the employees of the undertaking who are responsible for railway safety or railway traffic control have necessary qualifications and are able to ensure the required level of safety for the services provided; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ettev&otilde;tja vedurijuhil on vastav juhiluba ja vajalik kvalifikatsioon; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the locomotive drivers of the undertaking hold an appropriate driver's licence and necessary qualifications; </inglise>
<eesti>6) ettev&otilde;tjale antud tegevusluba ei ole varem kehtetuks tunnistatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 13 alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the operating licence issued to the undertaking has not been previously revoked on the basis of &sect; 13 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>7) ettev&otilde;tja on finantsmajanduslikult v&otilde;imeline t&auml;itma oma kohustusi, muuhulgas on ta v&otilde;imeline t&auml;itma oma tegelikke ja v&otilde;imalikke kohustusi v&auml;hemalt 12 kuu jooksul ning tal ei ole maksuv&otilde;lgnevusi; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the undertaking is able to perform its financial obligations and is able to perform its actual and potential obligations for a period of at least twelve months; the undertaking has no tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>8) ettev&otilde;tjal on vastutuskindlustus oma kohustuste t&auml;itmataj&auml;tmisest v&otilde;i mitten&otilde;uetekohasest t&auml;itmisest tekkinud kahju h&uuml;vitamiseks vastavalt &otilde;igusaktidele ja riikidevahelistele kokkulepetele; </eesti>
<inglise>8) the undertaking has liability insurance in order to compensate pursuant to legislation and international agreements, for damages due failure to perform its obligations or inadequate performance thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>9) ettev&otilde;tja raudteeinfrastruktuur v&otilde;i raudteeveerem vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja selle alusel kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>9) the railway infrastructure or the rail vehicle of the undertaking complies with the requirements established by this Act and on the basis thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 l&otilde;igetes 4 ja 5 nimetatud tegevusloa saamiseks ei kohaldata k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 4, 5 ja 9 nimetatud tingimusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The requirements specified in clauses (1) 4), 5) and 9) of this section do not apply to obtainment of operating licences specified in subsections 8 (4) and (5) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa taotlemiseks vajalikud dokumendid </eesti>
<inglise>Documents necessary for application for operating licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa taotleja esitab Raudteeametile j&auml;rgmised dokumendid: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person who applies for an operating licence shall submit the following documents to the Railway Administration: </inglise>
<eesti>1) avaldus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an application; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul p&otilde;hikiri v&otilde;i &uuml;hinguleping; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in the case of a company, the articles of association or the partnership agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>3) asutamisel oleva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul asutamislepingu notariaalselt t&otilde;estatud &auml;rakiri; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the case of a company being founded, a notarised copy of the memorandum of association; </inglise>
<eesti>4) tegutseva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul &auml;riregistri v&auml;ljav&otilde;te, samuti majandusaasta aruanne, mis on koostatud ja kinnitatud mitte varem kui kuus kuud enne avalduse esitamist, ning Maksuameti kohaliku asutuse t&otilde;end maksuv&otilde;lgnevuste puudumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) in the case of an operating company, an extract from the commercial register, the annual report prepared and approved not earlier than six months before the submission of the application, and a certificate of the local agency of the Tax Board concerning the absence of tax arrears; </inglise>
<eesti>5) &auml;ri&uuml;hingut juhtima &otilde;igustatud isikute v&otilde;i juhatuse liikmete nimekiri, milles m&auml;rgitakse liikme ees- ja perekonnanimi, isikukood (selle puudumisel s&uuml;nniaeg), elukoht, andmed hariduse v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;alase kogemuse ja viimaste t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistuskohtade kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a list of persons who have the right to manage the company, or of the members of the management board of the company; the list shall set out the given names and surnames of the members, their personal identification codes (or, in the absence thereof, the date of birth), residences, information concerning their education or professional experience, and their recent places of work or service; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kirjalik kinnitus k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2-5 nimetatud isikute vastavuse kohta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a written confirmation concerning the compliance of the persons specified in clauses 9 (1) 2) -5) of this Act with the established requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>7) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 8 nimetatud vastutuskindlustuse leping v&otilde;i asutamisel oleva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul kindlustusettev&otilde;tte kinnitus kindlustuslepingu s&otilde;lmimise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the liability insurance contract specified in clause 9 (1) 8) of this Act or, in the case of a company being founded, a confirmation from an insurance enterprise concerning the entry into an insurance contract; </inglise>
<eesti>8) ettev&otilde;tja kehtiv ohutustunnistus v&otilde;i asutamisel oleva &auml;ri&uuml;hingu puhul kinnitus ohutustunnistuse v&auml;ljaandmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>8) a valid safety certificate of the undertaking or, in the case of a company being founded, a confirmation concerning the issue of a safety certificate; </inglise>
<eesti>9) dokument riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>9) a document certifying the payment of the state fee. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeametile esitatud dokumendid ei kuulu avaldamisele kolmandatele isikutele, kui seadustes ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Documents submitted to the Railway Administration are not subject to disclosure to third persons unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa andmine ja andmisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Issue of operating licences and refusal to issue operating licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa andmise v&otilde;i andmisest keeldumise otsustab Raudteeamet &uuml;he kuu jooksul avalduse esitamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Railway Administration shall decide on the issue of an operating licence or refusal to issue an operating licence within one month after the submission of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa andmine vormistatakse Raudteeameti peadirektori k&auml;skkirjaga ja tegevusluba j&otilde;ustub k&auml;skkirjas n&auml;idatud kuup&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The issue of an operating licence shall be documented by a directive of the Director General of the Railway Administration, and the operating licence enters into force on the date indicated in the directive. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;skkirja &auml;rakiri ja tegevusluba edastatakse taotlejale hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;skkirja allakirjutamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>A copy of the directive and the operating licence shall be sent to the applicant not later than within three working days after the signing of the directive. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeamet keeldub tegevusloa andmisest, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Railway Administration shall refuse to issue an operating licence if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tja ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 9 nimetatud tingimustele; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the undertaking does not comply with the requirements specified in &sect; 9 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettev&otilde;tja ei ole esitanud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud dokumente; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the undertaking fails to submit the documents specified in subsection 10 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) esitatud dokumendid on eba&otilde;iged v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the submitted documents are inaccurate or incomplete. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa andmisest keeldumine vormistatakse Raudteeameti peadirektori k&auml;skkirjaga, mis peab sisaldama keeldumise p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A refusal to issue an operating licence shall be documented by a directive of the Director General of the Railway Administration which shall contain the reason for the refusal. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Raudteeametil on &otilde;igus m&auml;&auml;rata taotlejale t&auml;htaeg tegevusloa andmist takistavate asjaolude k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Railway Administration has the right to grant an applicant a term for the elimination of circumstances which prevent the issue of an operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Taotlejal on &otilde;igus nimetatud t&auml;htaja jooksul esitada t&auml;iendavaid dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>The applicant has the right to submit additional documents during the specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui taotleja ei k&otilde;rvalda takistavaid asjaolusid v&otilde;i ei esita t&auml;iendavaid dokumente m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks, keeldub Raudteeamet tegevusloa andmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>If the applicant fails to eliminate the circumstances preventing the issue of an operating licence or to submit additional documents during the specified term, the Railway Administration shall refuse to issue the operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtivuse tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Conditions for validity of operating licence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Asutamisel olev &auml;ri&uuml;hing, kellele Raudteeamet on andnud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 l&otilde;igetes 1-3 nimetatud tegevusloa, on kohustatud enne tegevusloas n&auml;idatud tegevuse alustamist esitama Raudteeametile p&otilde;hikirja ja &auml;riregistri v&auml;ljav&otilde;tte, samuti &sect; 10 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 6-9 nimetatud dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A company being founded to which the Railway Administration has issued an operating licence specified in subsections 8 (1) -(3) of this Act is required to submit the articles of association, an extract from the commercial register, and the documents specified in clauses 10 (1) 6) -9) of this Act to the Railway Administration before commencement of the activities indicated in the operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeametil on &otilde;igus igal ajal kontrollida ettev&otilde;tja vastavust tegevusloa saamise tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Railway Administration has the right to verify the compliance of an undertaking with the conditions for the obtainment of the operating licence at any time. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tegevusloa andmise aluseks olnud asjaolud on muutunud, on ettev&otilde;tja kohustatud viivitamata teatama Raudteeametile toimunud muudatustest ja esitama vastavad dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of changes in the circumstances on the basis of which an operating licence is issued, the undertaking is required to notify the Railway Administration immediately of the changes and submit the corresponding documents. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of operating licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa v&otilde;ib tunnistada kehtetuks, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An operating licence may be revoked if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) raudteeinfrastruktuur v&otilde;i raudteeveerem ei vasta kehtivatele ohutusn&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja tegevus ei taga ohutusn&otilde;uete t&auml;itmist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the railway infrastructure or the rail vehicle does not comply with the safety requirements currently in force, or if the activities of the undertaking do not ensure compliance with the safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettev&otilde;tja ei ole kuue kuu jooksul tegutsenud tegevusloas nimetatud tegevusalal; </eesti>
<inglise>2) for six months, the undertaking has not operated in the area of activity indicated in the operating licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettev&otilde;tja ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 9 nimetatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the undertaking does not comply with the requirements specified in &sect; 9 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeamet on kohustatud enne tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise otsustamist m&auml;&auml;rama ettev&otilde;tjale ettekirjutuse alusel t&auml;htaja kehtetuks tunnistamise aluseks olevate puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Before deciding on the revocation of an operating licence, the Railway Administration shall determine, on the basis of a precept, a term for the undertaking for the elimination of deficiencies which constitute the basis for revocation. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui ettev&otilde;tja ei k&otilde;rvalda tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamise aluseks olevaid puudusi m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks, tunnistab Raudteeamet tegevusloa kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>If the undertaking fails to eliminate the deficiencies which constitute the basis for the revocation of the operating licence during the specified term, the Railway Administration shall revoke the operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaliku raudteeveoteenuse osutamise tagamiseks v&otilde;ib Raudteeamet anda ajutise tegevusloa raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjale, kelle tegevusluba tunnistatakse kehtetuks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 7 ja 8 etten&auml;htud alustel tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamisest arvates, kuid mitte kauemaks kui kuueks kuuks, mille jooksul on raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja kohustatud j&auml;tkama tegevust ajutises tegevusloas n&auml;idatud tingimustel ja ulatuses. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Railway Administration may, in order to ensure the provision of public rail transport services, issue a temporary operating licence to a railway undertaking whose operating licence is revoked on the grounds prescribed in clauses 9 (1) 7) or 8) of this Act, after the revocation of the operating licence, but not for longer than six months during which the railway undertaking is required to continue its activities under the conditions and to the extent indicated in the temporary operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine vormistatakse Raudteeameti peadirektori k&auml;skkirjaga ja tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamine j&otilde;ustub k&auml;skkirjas n&auml;idatud kuup&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The revocation of an operating licence shall be documented by a directive of the Director General of the Railway Administration and the revocation enters into force on the date indicated in the directive. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;skkirja &auml;rakiri edastatakse ettev&otilde;tjale, kelle tegevusluba tunnistati kehtetuks, ja k&otilde;igile raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjatele viivitamata, kuid mitte hiljem kui k&uuml;mne t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;skkirja allakirjutamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>A copy of a directive shall be sent to the undertaking whose operating licence is revoked and to all other railway undertakings immediately, but not later than within ten working days after the signing of the directive. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of validity of operating licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Tegevusloa kehtivus l&otilde;peb: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The validity of an operating licence shall terminate: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tja l&otilde;ppemisel, sealhulgas &auml;ri&uuml;hingu &uuml;hinemisel ja jaotumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon the dissolution of the undertaking, including the merger or division of the company; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon the revocation of the operating licence; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>3) at the request of the undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa kehtivuse l&otilde;ppemise teadaanne avaldatakse Riigi Teataja Lisas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A notice concerning the termination of validity of an operating licence shall be published in the Riigi Teataja Lisa. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevusloa kehtivuse l&otilde;petamine ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of validity of operating licence at request of undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib esitada taotluse Raudteeametile tegevusloa kehtivuse l&otilde;petamiseks v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud enne tegevusloa kehtivuse soovitavat l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An undertaking may submit an application to the Railway Administration for the termination of the validity of the operating licence at least six months before the desired termination of the validity of the operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tegevusloa kehtivuse l&otilde;petamine ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel vormistatakse Raudteeameti peadirektori k&auml;skkirjaga ja tegevusloa kehtivuse l&otilde;petamine j&otilde;ustub k&auml;skkirjas n&auml;idatud p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The termination of the validity of an operating licence at the request of an undertaking shall be documented by a directive of the Director General of the Railway Administration, and the termination enters into force on the date indicated in the directive. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;skkirja &auml;rakiri edastatakse taotlejale hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;skkirja allakirjutamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>A copy of a directive shall be sent to the applicant not later than within three working days after the signing of the directive. </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliiklus ja ohutus </eesti>
<inglise>Railway Traffic and Safety </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Ohutuse tagamine </eesti>
<inglise>Ensurance of safety </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud tagama ohutu liikluse oma raudteeinfrastruktuuril ja hoidma selle ohutust tagavalt t&ouml;&ouml;korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Railway infrastructure managers shall ensure safe traffic within their railway infrastructures and maintain the working order of the infrastructures such that safety is ensured. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud tagama raudteeveo ohutuse ja tema poolt kasutatava raudteeveeremi vastavuse kehtivatele ohutus- ja muudele n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>Rail transport undertakings shall ensure the safety of rail transport, and the compliance of the rail vehicles used by such undertakings with safety and other requirements currently in force. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud t&auml;itma k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 kohaselt kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid ja eeskirju ning k&otilde;iki keskkonna-, tule- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust, t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ning tervisekaitset puudutavaid eeskirju ja n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>Railway undertakings shall comply with the requirements and rules established according to subsection (2) of this section, and with all the rules and requirements related to environmental safety, fire safety, occupational safety, occupational health and public health protection. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri ja raudteeveeremi tehnoloogilised ja ekspluatatsioonin&otilde;uded, n&otilde;uded raudteeliiklusele ja raudteekorrashoiule, samuti n&otilde;uded raudteevedudele s&auml;testatakse teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;rusega kinnitatud raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Technological and operational requirements for railway infrastructure and rail vehicles, requirements for railway traffic and maintenance, and requirements for rail transport shall be provided for in the rules for technical use of railways approved by a regulation of the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettev&otilde;tja, kes taotleb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tegevusluba, peab eelnevalt saama Raudteeametilt ohutustunnistuse, mis kinnitab, et tema raudteeinfrastruktuur ja raudteeliikluse korraldus vastavad raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An undertaking which applies for the operating licence specified in subsection 8 (1) of this Act shall obtain a safety certificate from the Railway Administration in advance which confirms that the railway infrastructure and the management of railway traffic of the undertaking comply with the requirements established in the rules for technical use. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.03.2001 entered into force 01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ettev&otilde;tja, kes taotleb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 8 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud tegevusluba, peab eelnevalt saama Raudteeametilt ohutustunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An undertaking which applies for an operating licence specified in subsections 8 (2) or (3) of this Act shall obtain a safety certificate from the Railway Administration in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>Ohutustunnistuse saamiseks peab ettev&otilde;tja esitama raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjale, kelle avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee raudteeinfrastruktuuri ta kavatseb kasutada, kinnituse, et tema raudteeveerem vastab raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele ja et tema vedurimeeskond vastab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 19 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to obtain a safety certificate, an undertaking shall submit confirmation to the railway infrastructure manager whose railway infrastructure designated for public use the undertaking intends to use that the rail vehicles of the undertaking comply with the requirements established in the rules for technical use of railways, and that the locomotive crews of the undertaking comply with the requirements provided for in &sect; 19 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.03.2001 entered into force 01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ohutustunnistuste v&auml;ljaandmise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the procedure for issue of safety certificates. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse ohutuse tagamiseks kehtestab sotsiaalminister Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud t&ouml;&ouml;de loetelu alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele eelneva ja perioodilise tervisekontrolli n&otilde;uded. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to ensure the safety of railway traffic, the Minister of Social Affairs shall, on the basis of the list of jobs established by the Government of the Republic, establish the requirements for advance and routine medical examinations of employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Raudteeametil on &otilde;igus igal ajal kontrollida raudteeliikluse ohutust ja raudteeveeremi vastavust kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Railway Administration has the right to verify the safety of railway traffic and the conformity of rail vehicles with the established requirements at any time. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeametil on kohustus kontrollida raudteeinfrastruktuuri ja raudteeveeremi vastavust kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele teede- ja sideministri m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaegadel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The Railway Administration is required to verify the conformity of railway infrastructure and rail vehicles with the established requirements during the terms and pursuant to the procedure determined by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud lubama riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet teostavatel isikutel igal ajal kontrollida raudteeinfrastruktuuri ja raudteeveeremi ning raudteeliikluse ohutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Railway undertakings are required to permit the persons exercising state supervision to verify the safety of railway infrastructure, rail vehicles and railway traffic at any time. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Raudteeametil on &otilde;igus teha raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjale ettekirjutusi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 alusel raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas kehtestatud n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmiseks ja ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral algatada tegevusloa kehtetuks tunnistamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The Railway Administration has the right to issue precepts to a railway undertaking for compliance with the requirements established on the basis of subsection (2) of this section in the rules for technical use of railways and, in the case of failure to comply with a precept, to initiate the revocation of an operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.03.2001 entered into force 01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas kehtestatud n&otilde;uete rikkumise korral, mis toob kaasa otsese ohu raudteeliiklusele, on raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjal &otilde;igus k&otilde;rvaldada raudteeinfrastruktuurilt raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele mittevastav raudteeveerem v&otilde;i v&otilde;tta viivitamata tarvitusele k&otilde;ik abin&otilde;ud, et tagada raudteeliikluse ohutus. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) In the case of a violation of the requirements established in the rules for technical use of railway which results in a direct danger to railway traffic, the railway infrastructure manager has the right to remove a rail vehicle which does not comply with the requirements established in the rules for technical use of railway from the railway infrastructure, or to immediately take all measures to ensure the safety of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirja rikkunud raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjale sellest tekkinud kahju ei h&uuml;vitata. </eesti>
<inglise>A rail transport undertaking which violates the rules for technical use of railway shall not be compensated for damage caused by such violation. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;igist raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirja rikkumistest on raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja kohustatud viivitamata teatama Raudteeametile </eesti>
<inglise>Railway infrastructure managers shall immediately notify the Railway Administration of all violations of the rules for technical use of railway. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.03.2001 entered into force 01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja tegevuseeskiri </eesti>
<inglise>Operating rules of railway infrastructure managers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteed majandab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja oma tegevuseeskirja alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A railway infrastructure manager shall manage a railway designated for public use on the basis of the operating rules of the railway infrastructure manager. </inglise>
<eesti>Tegevuseeskirjas kehtestatakse raudteeinfrastruktuuri korrashoiu, raudteeliikluse korraldamise ja raudteeinfrastruktuuri raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele kasutada andmise tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>In the operating rules, conditions for the maintenance of railway infrastructure, the organisation of railway traffic and the grant of the use of railway infrastructure to railway undertakings are established. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tegevuseeskirja ja sinna tehtud muudatuste heakskiitmise otsustab Raudteeamet raudteeinfrastruktuuriettev&otilde;tja vastava avalduse esitamisest &uuml;he kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The approval of the operating rules specified in subsection (1) of this section and the approval of amendments to such rules shall be decided by the Railway Administration within one month after the railway infrastructure manager has submitted a corresponding application. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeamet v&otilde;ib tegevuseeskirja ja tegevuseeskirja muudatuste heakskiitmisest keelduda ja n&otilde;uda nende muutmist v&otilde;i tunnistada need kehtetuks, kui need on vastuolus seaduste v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 16 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Railway Administration may refuse to approve the operating rules and amendments to such rules and request the amendment thereof or declare the rules invalid if the operating rules or amendments thereto are contrary to law or the rules for technical use of railway specified in subsection 16 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tegevuseeskiri tuleb avaldada ja teha k&auml;ttesaadavaks Raudteeameti peadirektori poolt kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud v&auml;ljaandes ja aadressidel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The operating rules specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be published and made available in the publication and at the addresses determined by the Director General of the Railway Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tegevuseeskirja muutmine j&otilde;ustub Raudteeameti otsuses m&auml;rgitud p&auml;eval, kuid mitte varem kui 45 p&auml;eva m&ouml;&ouml;dudes tegevuseeskirja muudatuste avaldamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Amendments to operating rules shall enter into force on the date set out in a decision of the Railway Administration, but not earlier than forty-five days after the publication of such amendments. </inglise>
<eesti>(06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.03.2001 entered into force 01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse juhtimise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to control railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja raudteeohutuse ja raudteeliikluse juhtimise eest vastutavatel t&ouml;&ouml;tajatel peab olema vastav kvalifikatsioonitunnistus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The employees of a railway infrastructure manager who are responsible for railway safety or railway traffic control must hold appropriate qualification certificates. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kvalifikatsioonitunnistuse saamiseks vajalikud ettevalmistus- ja kutsesobivusn&otilde;uded kinnitab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall approve the requirements for training and professional suitability necessary for the obtainment of a qualification certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib kehtestada raudteeohutuse ja raudteeliikluse juhtimise eest vastutavatele t&ouml;&ouml;tajatele k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;uetest k&otilde;rgemaid n&otilde;udeid kvalifikatsioonitunnistuste v&auml;ljastamise eeskirjas. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Railway infrastructure managers may establish in the rules for issue of qualification certificates higher requirements than those specified in subsection (2) of this section for employees responsible for railway safety or railway traffic control. </inglise>
<eesti>Kvalifikatsioonitunnistuse annab v&auml;lja raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>Qualification certificates shall be issued by railway infrastructure managers. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeametil on &otilde;igus kontrollida raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja raudteeohutuse ja raudteeliikluse juhtimise eest vastutavate t&ouml;&ouml;tajate vastavust k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Railway Administration has the right to verify whether the employees of a railway infrastructure manager who are responsible for railway safety or railway traffic control comply with the requirements specified in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeveeremi juhtimise &otilde;igus </eesti>
<inglise>Right to drive rail vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeveoteenuse osutamiseks vajalikku raudteeveeremit v&otilde;ib juhtida raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja vedurimeeskond, kes koosneb v&auml;hemalt kahest liikmest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Rail vehicles necessary for the provision of rail transport services may be driven by locomotive crews of rail transport undertakings which consist of at least two members. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeveeremit v&otilde;ib juhtida isik, kellel on Eestis v&auml;lja antud v&otilde;i v&auml;lisriigis v&auml;lja antud ja Eestis tunnustatud vedurijuhiluba. </eesti>
<inglise>Rail vehicles may be driven by a person who holds a locomotive driver's licence issued in Estonia or a locomotive driver's licence issued in a foreign state and recognised in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud vedurijuhiloa saamiseks taotleja kutsesobivusele, teadmistele, oskustele ja kogemustele vajalikud n&otilde;uded kehtestab teede- ja sideminister, v&otilde;ttes arvesse sotsiaalministri kehtestatud n&otilde;udeid taotleja terviseseisundile. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Transport and Communications shall establish the requirements for the professional suitability, knowledge, skills and experience of persons who apply for a locomotive driver's licence specified in subsection (1) of this section, taking into account the requirements established by the Minister of Social Affairs for the state of health of the applicants. </inglise>
<eesti>Vedurijuhiloa v&auml;ljaandmise eeskirjad ja eksamineerimise korra kehtestab teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>Rules for issue of locomotive driver's licences and the procedure for examinations shall be established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeveeremi juhtimise &otilde;igus v&otilde;etakse &auml;ra arstliku komisjoni otsuse alusel isikult, kelle terviseseisund ei vasta kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On the basis of a decision of a medical committee, a person whose state of health does not comply with the established requirements shall be deprived of the right to drive rail vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeveeremi juhtimise &otilde;igus v&otilde;idakse &auml;ra v&otilde;tta v&otilde;i t&uuml;histada raudteeliikluse n&otilde;udeid rikkunud isikult, olenevalt tema toimepandud rikkumise iseloomust ja raskusastmest, ainult seadustega s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A person who violates railway traffic requirements may be deprived of the right to drive rail vehicles or such right may be revoked depending on the nature and severity of the violation only pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja vedurimeeskond peab vastama selle raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja, kelle raudteel nad s&otilde;idavad, tegevuseeskirjas etten&auml;htud s&otilde;idukogemuse n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A locomotive crew of a rail transport undertaking shall comply with the requirements for driving experience prescribed in the operating rules of the railway infrastructure manager on whose railways the crew drives. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjal on &otilde;igus mitte lubada raudteeveeremit juhtima vedurijuhti, kes on tarvitanud alkoholi, narkootilisi, ps&uuml;hhotroopseid v&otilde;i ps&uuml;hhotoksilisi aineid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Railway infrastructure managers have the right to prohibit locomotive drivers who have consumed alcohol, narcotic, psychotropic or other psychotoxic substances from driving rail vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee-ehitus ja ehitusj&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>Railway construction and construction supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri rajatisi, sealhulgas raudteed v&otilde;ib ehitada vastavalt planeerimis- ja ehitusseaduses (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 29, 399) s&auml;testatule vaid Raudteeameti poolt eelnevalt heakskiidetud ehituskava kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Railway infrastructure constructions, including railways, may be constructed in accordance with the provisions of the Planning and Building Act (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 27, 380; 29, 398, 399; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348; 2001, 42, 235) only according to the construction plans approved by the Railway Administration in advance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kava heakskiitmine ei ole vajalik, kui raudteeinfrastruktuuri rajatiste tehnoloogiline &uuml;mberseadmestamine, rekonstrueerimine v&otilde;i renoveerimine ei too kaasa raudteeliikluse sulgemist kauemaks kui &uuml;heks &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks v&otilde;i kui raudtee pealisehituse remont on tingitud erakorralistest asjaoludest, mis v&otilde;ivad ohustada raudteeliiklust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The approval of the plans specified in subsection (1) of this section is not required if the technological re-equipment, reconstruction or renovation of railway infrastructure constructions does not result in the closure of railway traffic for more than a twenty-four hour period or if the repair of railway superstructure is necessary due to extraordinary circumstances which may endanger railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee ja sellega liituva raudtee r&ouml;&ouml;bastee laius on 1520 mm. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The width of railway tracks designated for public use and the railway tracks connecting thereto shall be 1520 mm. </inglise>
<eesti>R&ouml;&ouml;bastee muu laiuse korral toimub raudtee-ehitus ja kasutuselev&otilde;tmine Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Railways with any other width of tracks shall be constructed and taken into service pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri rajatiste projekteerimistingimused v&auml;ljastab kohalik omavalitsus koosk&otilde;lastatult Raudteeametiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Design criteria for railway infrastructure constructions shall be issued by local governments in co-ordination with the Railway Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri rajatiste ehitusj&auml;relevalvet planeerimis- ja ehitusseaduse &sect; 50 t&auml;henduses teostab Raudteeamet, koosk&otilde;lastades raudteeinfrastruktuuri rajatiste projekti, ehitusloa ja kasutusloa v&auml;ljaandmise kohaliku omavalitsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>The Railway Administration shall exercise construction supervision as defined in &sect; 50 of the Planning and Building Act over railway infrastructure constructions, co-ordinating the issue of the building designs, building permits and permits for the use of railway infrastructure constructions with local governments. </inglise>
<eesti>Ehitusj&auml;relevalve teostamiseks m&auml;&auml;rab Raudteeamet igale ehitusele litsentseeritud raudtee-ehituse j&auml;relevalveinseneri. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of construction supervision, the Railway Administration shall appoint a licensed railway construction supervising engineer for each construction. </inglise>
<eesti>Ehitusj&auml;relevalvega seonduvad kulud kannab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>Costs related to construction supervision shall be borne by the railway infrastructure manager. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ehitusj&auml;relevalve teostamise korra ja ehitamise dokumenteerimise n&otilde;uded kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Government of the Republic shall establish the procedure for the exercise of construction supervision and the requirements for the documentation of construction. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee-ehituse j&auml;relevalveinseneri litsentseerimise korra ja j&auml;relevalveinseneri &otilde;igused kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic shall establish the procedure for licensing railway construction supervising engineers, and the rights of supervising engineers. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee raudteeinfrastruktuuri ehitamiseks ja korrashoiuks v&otilde;ib riik anda toetust, mille suurus m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks igal aastal riigieelarves. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The state may grant aid for the construction and maintenance of the infrastructure of railways designated for public use and the amount of the aid shall be determined annually in the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;nd </eesti>
<inglise>Railway protection zone </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudtee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;nd on raudtee sihtotstarbelise tegevuse ja h&auml;ireteta raudteeliikluse tagamiseks ning raudteelt l&auml;htuvate kahjulike m&otilde;jude v&auml;hendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The purpose of railway protection zones is to ensure trouble-free railway traffic and the operation of railways according to their intended purpose, and to reduce the damaging effects of railways. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudtee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndi laiuseks on r&ouml;&ouml;pa teljest (mitmeteelistel raudteedel ja jaamades &auml;&auml;rmise r&ouml;&ouml;pa teljest) linnades ja asulates 30 meetrit, v&auml;ljaspool linnu ja asulaid 50 meetrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The width of a railway protection zone shall be 30 metres from the axis of the rail (on multiple track railways and in stations, from the axis of the outermost rail) in cities and settlements, and 50 metres outside cities and settlements. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudtee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis asuva kinnisasja valdaja ei tohi oma tegevuse v&otilde;i tegevusetusega takistada raudtee sihtotstarbelist kasutamist, halvendada raudtee korrashoidu ega ohustada liiklust. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Possessors of immovables located in railway protection zones may not, by their acts or omissions, hinder the use of railways in accordance with their designated purpose, damage the condition of railways or endanger traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudtee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis v&otilde;ib maaparanduss&uuml;steemide rajamine, maavara kaevandamine, kaevamist&ouml;&ouml;de teostamine, metsa lageraie ja muud looduskeskkonda muutvad t&ouml;&ouml;d, hoonete ja rajatiste ehitamine, kergestis&uuml;ttivate ainete ja l&otilde;hkeainete tootmine ja ladustamine, samuti seadmete ja materjalide ladustamine ja paigaldamine, mis seab ohtu n&auml;htavuse kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis, toimuda vaid vastava raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja eelneval kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul, millega v&otilde;ib kehtestada raudtee kaitsev&ouml;&ouml;ndis teostatavatele t&ouml;&ouml;dele t&auml;iendavaid n&otilde;udeid. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Within a railway protection zone, construction of soil improvement systems, extraction of mineral resources, conduct of excavation operations, clear cutting of forest and other work which changes the natural environment, construction of buildings and constructions, production and storage of inflammable substances or explosives, and storage or installation of equipment or materials in a manner which reduces visibility in the protection zone may be conducted only with the prior written consent of the corresponding railway infrastructure manager, by which additional requirements may be established for work conducted within the railway protection zone. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee&uuml;letuskohad </eesti>
<inglise>Railway crossings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) S&otilde;idukid, jalak&auml;ijad ja aetavad kariloomad v&otilde;ivad raudteed &uuml;letada ainult selleks etten&auml;htud ja t&auml;histatud raudtee&uuml;les&otilde;idukohtades ning jalak&auml;ijad raudtee&uuml;lek&auml;igukohtades liikluseeskirjas s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Vehicles, pedestrians and driven cattle may cross railways only on railway crossings prescribed and marked for that purpose, and pedestrians may cross railways only on railway crossings pursuant to the procedure provided for in the traffic rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud tagama raudtee&uuml;les&otilde;idukoha ja -&uuml;lek&auml;igukoha korrashoiu ja liikluskorraldusvahendite paigaldamise ning raudteeohutuse raudteemaal tehnokasutuseeskirjas s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Railway infrastructure managers are required to ensure the maintenance of railway crossings and the installation of traffic control devices, and railway safety on railway ground areas on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided for in the rules for technical use. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse ajutised piirangud ja sulgemine </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary restriction or closure of railway traffic </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeliiklust v&otilde;ib raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteel ajutiselt sulgeda kuni &uuml;heks &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Railway traffic on a railway designated for public use may be temporarily closed by the railway infrastructure manager for up to one twenty-four hour period. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliiklust v&otilde;ib avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteel ajutiselt sulgeda kauemaks kui &uuml;heks &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;evaks v&otilde;i oluliselt piirata Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Railway traffic on railways designated for public use may be temporarily closed for more than a twenty-four hour period or substantially restricted pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri v&otilde;i raudteeveeremi seisundist raudteeliiklusele tuleneva otsese ohu korral on raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja kohustatud tarvitusele v&otilde;tma k&otilde;ik abin&otilde;ud, mis on vajalikud ohutu liikluse tagamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of a direct danger to railway traffic arising from the condition of a railway infrastructure or rail vehicle, the railway infrastructure manager is required to take all measures necessary to ensure safe traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud juhul on raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjal &otilde;igus raudteeliiklus sulgeda v&otilde;i seda oluliselt piirata, teatades viivitamata ohutuse tagamiseks tarvituselev&otilde;etud abin&otilde;udest Raudteeametile. </eesti>
<inglise>In such case, the railway infrastructure manager has the right to close or substantially restrict railway traffic, immediately notifying the Railway Administration of the measures taken to ensure safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) M&otilde;juval p&otilde;hjusel, eelk&otilde;ige, kui raudteeliiklusega ohustatakse inimeste elu v&otilde;i tervist v&otilde;i keskkonda, on Raudteeameti selleks volitatud ametnikul igal ajal &otilde;igus teha raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjale ettekirjutus raudteeliikluse sulgemiseks v&otilde;i oluliseks piiramiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) With good reason, especially if railway traffic endangers human life, health or the environment, an authorised official of the Railway Administration has the right to issue at any time a precept to a railway infrastructure manager for the closure or substantial restriction of railway traffic. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteel toimunud &otilde;nnetuse korral on riigi ja kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;lesandeks oma asutuste kaudu osutada igak&uuml;lgset kaasabi &otilde;nnetuse tagaj&auml;rgede likvideerimiseks ja raudteeliikluse v&otilde;imalikult kiireks taastamiseks p&auml;&auml;steseaduses (RT I 1994, 28, 424; 1998, 39, 598) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of railway accident, the state and local governments, through their agencies, are required to provide all possible assistance to remedy the effects of the accident and restore railway traffic as quickly as possible pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Rescue Act (RT I 1994, 28, 424; 1998, 39, 598). </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Avalik-&otilde;iguslikud kitsendused raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate tegevusele </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions in Public Law on Activities of Railway Undertakings </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Juurdep&auml;&auml;s avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee raudteeinfrastruktuurile </eesti>
<inglise>Access to infrastructure of railways designated for public use </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjal on &otilde;igus raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamistasu, -aja ja muude kasutamistingimuste osas diskrimineerimata kasutada avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteed raudteeveoteenuse osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Rail transport undertakings have the right to use railways designated for public use for the provision of rail transport services without discrimination with regard to user fees, time and other conditions of use of the railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamisel tagatakse &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamiseks vajalike rongiliinide eraldamine esimese eelistusena. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In distribution of railway infrastructure capacity, allocation of railway infrastructure capacity to train paths necessary for the provision of public utility transport services shall have first priority. </inglise>
<eesti>Teise eelistusena on &otilde;igus saada l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjal avaliku raudteeveoteenuse osutamiseks rahvusvahelises otse&uuml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise>Rail transport undertakings shall have second priority in the allocation of railway infrastructure capacity for the provision public rail transport services in international direct connection. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>L&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamine avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteel </eesti>
<inglise>Distribution of capacity on railways designated for public use </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud jaotama avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudtee raudteeinfrastruktuuri l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime, eraldades l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime &uuml;hiskondliku veoteenuse osutamiseks ning seej&auml;rel eraldades jaotamisele kuuluva l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime teistele raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjatele avaliku konkursi alusel, arvestades &sect; 24 l&otilde;ikes 2 etten&auml;htud eelistust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Railway infrastructure managers are required to distribute the infrastructure capacity of railways designated for public use by allocating capacity for the provision of public utility transport services, thereafter allocating capacity subject to distribution to other rail transport undertakings on the basis of a public competition, taking into account the priorities prescribed in subsection 24 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamise avaliku konkursi tingimused ja korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The Government of the Republic shall establish the conditions and procedure for public competitions for distribution of railway infrastructure capacity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja, kellele eraldati l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa, ja raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja lepivad kokku raudteeinfrastruktuurile juurdep&auml;&auml;su &uuml;ksikasjades, eriti kasutamise ajas ja kestuses, samuti kasutamistasus ja teistes kasutamistingimustes. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A rail transport undertaking to whom capacity is allocated and the railway infrastructure manager shall agree on the details for access to the railway infrastructure, in particular on the time and duration of use, and on user fee and other conditions of use. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud kokkulepe peab olema s&otilde;lmitud kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>Such agreement shall be entered into in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>Kasutamistasu ning kasutamise aja ja kestuse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramisel tuleb eelk&otilde;ige arvesse v&otilde;tta teenuse iseloomu ja kestust, turuolukorda ning raudteeinfrastruktuuri kulumi astet, samuti veeremi koosseisu, seisundit ja veokiirust. </eesti>
<inglise>In determination of the user fee, and the time and duration of use, the nature and duration of the service, the market situation, the level of wear and tear of the railway infrastructure, the composition, condition and transport speed of the rail vehicle shall be primarily taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>Kasutamistasu m&auml;&auml;ratakse Raudteeameti kehtestatud raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamise tasu arvestamise metoodika alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>User fees shall be determined pursuant to the methodology established by the Railway Administration for the calculation of fees for the use of railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjal ei ole &otilde;igust talle eraldatud l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa mis tahes viisil &uuml;le anda ega loovutada ning ta on kohustatud talle eraldatud l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa kasutama lepinguga etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A rail transport undertaking does not have the right to transfer or assign the capacity allocated to the undertaking in any manner, and the undertaking is required to use the capacity allocated to it pursuant to the procedure prescribed by the agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud n&otilde;uete rikkumise korral kuulub eraldatud l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa &auml;rav&otilde;tmisele ning jaotamisele k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of violation of these requirements, the allocated capacity is subject to withdrawal and distribution pursuant to the procedure provided for in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjal on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kaebusega Raudteeameti poole, kui raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja ei jaotanud vaba l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imet k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras v&otilde;i kui raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjale ei eraldatud l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa v&otilde;i eraldati diskrimineerivatel tingimustel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A rail transport undertaking has the right to file a complaint with the Railway Administration if a railway infrastructure manager fails to distribute free capacity on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided by this Act, or if a rail transport undertaking is not allocated capacity or capacity is allocated to it under discriminatory conditions. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeamet vaatab kaebuse l&auml;bi ja otsustab, kas l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamine on toimunud koosk&otilde;las k&auml;esoleva seaduse ja konkurentsiseadusega (RT I 1998, 30, 410). </eesti>
<inglise>The Railway Administration shall hear such complaints and decide whether capacity was distributed in accordance with this Act and the Competition Act (RT I 1998, 30, 410; 1999, 89, 813; 2000, 53, 343; RT III 2000, 21, 232). </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeameti otsusega mitten&otilde;ustumisel on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon disagreement with a decision of the Railway Administration, a rail transport undertaking has the right of recourse to the court. </inglise>
<eesti>Kohtusse p&ouml;&ouml;rdumine ei ole eraldatud l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa &auml;rav&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i muutmise aluseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Filing with a court does not constitute a basis for the withdrawal or change of allocated capacity. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui Raudteeamet leiab, et l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamisel on rikutud k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud n&otilde;udeid, teeb Raudteeamet raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjale ettekirjutuse seaduserikkumise k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the Railway Administration finds that the requirements provided for in this Act are violated in the distribution of capacity, the Railway Administration shall issue a precept to the railway infrastructure manager for the elimination of the violation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Raamatupidamise eraldatus </eesti>
<inglise>Separate accounting </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad, kes osutavad avalikku raudteeveoteenust ja majandavad avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteed, peavad oma raamatupidamises pidama eraldi tulude ja kulude arvestust veoteenuse ja raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamise valdkondade osas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Railway undertakings which provide public rail transport services or manage railways designated for public use are required to keep separate accounting of the revenue and expenditure relating to the areas of transport services and the management of railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi poolt raudteeinfrastruktuuri majandamiseks antud toetuse ja &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamise eest tasutava h&uuml;vituse &uuml;lekandmine &uuml;hest valdkonnast teise on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>State aid granted for the management of infrastructure and compensation paid by the state for the provision of public utility transport services shall not be transferred from one area of activity to another. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle kohustuse j&auml;rgimine peab kajastuma m&otilde;lema valdkonna tulude ja kulude arvestuses. </eesti>
<inglise>Adherence to such requirement shall be reflected in the accounting of the revenue and expenditure of both areas of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja, kes osutab &uuml;hiskondlikke ja muid veoteenuseid, peab oma raamatupidamises pidama eraldi tulude ja kulude arvestust &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste ja teiste veoteenuste valdkondade osas. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rail transport undertakings which provide public utility transport services and other transport services are required to keep separate accounting of the revenue and expenditure relating to the areas of public utility transport services and other transport services. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigi poolt &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamise eest tasutava h&uuml;vituse kasutamine muus valdkonnas on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation paid by the state for the provision of public utility transport services shall not be used in any other area of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>Selle kohustuse j&auml;rgimine peab kajastuma m&otilde;lema valdkonna tulude ja kulude arvestuses. </eesti>
<inglise>Adherence to such requirement shall be reflected in the accounting of the revenue and expenditure of both areas of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolevas paragrahvis nimetatud raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad on kohustatud teede- ja sideministri kehtestatud korras ja t&auml;htaegadel esitama Raudteeametile k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igete 1 ja 2 kohaselt peetavate tulude ja kulude arvestused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Railway undertakings specified in this section are required to submit the accounting of revenue and expenditure kept according to subsections (1) and (2) of this section to the Railway Administration pursuant to the procedure and during the terms established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja, kellel on selleks &otilde;igustatud huvi, v&otilde;ib tutvuda Raudteeameti kehtestatud korras tulude ja kulude arvestustega. </eesti>
<inglise>Railway undertakings with legitimate interest may examine accounting of revenue and expenditure pursuant to the procedure established by the Railway Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hendus teiste raudteedega </eesti>
<inglise>Connection to other railways </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja, kelle raudtee piirneb v&otilde;i liitub teise raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja raudteega, peab lubama &uuml;henduse oma raudteeinfrastruktuuriga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Any railway infrastructure manager whose railway borders on or joins with a railway of another railway infrastructure manager shall permit connection to its railway infrastructure. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &uuml;henduse tingimused ja selle eest makstav tasu lepitakse kokku raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjate vahel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The railway infrastructure managers shall agree on the conditions of and fees paid for connection specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui &uuml;henduse tingimustes v&otilde;i tasus kokkulepet ei saavutata, on &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>If agreement on the conditions of connection and fees paid therefor cannot be reached, the railway infrastructure managers may have recourse to the court. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Veotingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Transport conditions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avalikku raudteeveoteenust v&otilde;ib osutada raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja veoeeskirja alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Public rail transport services may be provided by rail transport undertakings pursuant to the transport rules. </inglise>
<eesti>Veoeeskirjas kehtestatakse veotingimused reisijateveoks v&otilde;i veotingimused kauba v&otilde;i veeremi liikide alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Transport rules shall establish the transport conditions for the transport of passengers or the transport conditions on the basis of the types of goods or rail vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud veoeeskiri ei sisalda veotasu suurust. </eesti>
<inglise>Such transport rules shall not include the amounts of transport fees. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud veoeeskirjade heakskiitmise ja sinna tehtud muudatuste heakskiitmise otsustab Raudteeamet raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja vastava avalduse esitamisest &uuml;he kuu jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The approval of transport rules specified in subsection (1) of this section and the approval of amendments to such rules shall be decided by the Railway Administration within one month after the rail transport undertaking has submitted a corresponding application. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Tegevusloa taotlemisega &uuml;heaegselt heakskiitmiseks esitatud veoeeskiri loetakse heakskiidetuks tegevusloa j&otilde;ustumise p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Transport rules which are submitted for approval concurrently with the application for an operating licence shall be deemed to be approved on the date of entry into force of the operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeamet v&otilde;ib veoeeskirja ja veoeeskirja muudatuste heakskiitmisest keelduda v&otilde;i n&otilde;uda nende muutmist v&otilde;i kehtetuks tunnistamist, kui need on vastuolus seadustega v&otilde;i raudteeveo heade tavadega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Railway Administration may refuse to approve transport rules or amendments thereto, or require their amendment or revocation if such rules are contrary to the law or good rail transport practices. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud veoeeskiri tuleb avaldada ja teha k&auml;ttesaadavaks Raudteeameti peadirektori poolt kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud v&auml;ljaandes ja aadressidel. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Transport rules specified in subsection (1) of this section shall be published and made available in the publication and at the addresses determined by the Director General of the Railway Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Veoeeskirja muutmine j&otilde;ustub Raudteeameti otsuses m&auml;rgitud p&auml;eval, kuid mitte varem kui 45 p&auml;eva m&ouml;&ouml;dudes veoeeskirja muudatuste avaldamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Amendments to transport rules shall enter into force on the date set out in a decision of the Railway Administration, but not earlier than forty-five days after the publication of such amendments. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hiskondlikud veoteenused </eesti>
<inglise>Public utility transport services </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riik v&otilde;ib &uuml;ldistes huvides tellida avalikku raudteeveoteenust osutavalt raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjalt reisijate v&otilde;i kaupade raudteeveoteenust (&uuml;hiskondlik raudteeveoteenus). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The state may, in public interest, contract rail transport services for passengers or goods (public utility rail transport services) from rail transport undertakings which provide public rail transport service. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;hiskondlikku raudteeveoteenust osutav raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud vedama reisijaid v&otilde;i kaupu riigiga s&otilde;lmitud lepingus s&auml;testatud tingimustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Rail transport undertakings which provide public utility rail transport services are required to carry passengers or goods under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure provided for in the contract entered into with the state. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja kohustus on teavitada &uuml;hiskondliku raudteeveoteenuse kasutajaid teenuse hinnast. </eesti>
<inglise>Rail transport undertakings are required to inform the users of public utility transport services of the prices of the services. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamiseks s&otilde;lmivad riik Raudteeameti kaudu ja raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tja lepingu, mis peab sisaldama v&auml;hemalt allj&auml;rgnevaid tingimusi: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the provision of public utility transport services, the state through the Railway Administration and a rail transport undertaking shall enter into a contract which shall include at least the following conditions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) osutatavate teenuste iseloomu, mahtu, marsruuti, regulaarsust ja kvaliteeti; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to nature, volume, routes, schedules and quality of services provided; </inglise>
<eesti>2) veo tariifi ja selle arvestuse aluseid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) transport tariffs and the bases for their calculation; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigi poolt makstava h&uuml;vituse suurust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the amount of compensation paid by the state; </inglise>
<eesti>4) lepingu muutmist ja t&auml;iendamist reguleerivaid s&auml;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) provisions regulating amendment of the contract; </inglise>
<eesti>5) lepingu kehtivusaega; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the term of validity of the contract; </inglise>
<eesti>6) lepingu rikkumise korral kohaldatavaid leppetrahve. </eesti>
<inglise>6) penalties imposed in the case of violation of the contract. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjale &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamise eest makstava h&uuml;vituse suurus tuleb kindlaks m&auml;&auml;rata v&auml;hemalt &uuml;heks aastaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The amount of compensation paid to rail transport undertakings for the provision of public utility transport services shall be determined for one year at least. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjale &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamise eest makstav h&uuml;vitus peab katma v&auml;hemalt neid &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamisel tekkinud kulusid, sealhulgas raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamistasu, mida raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik katta nimetatud teenuste osutamisel saadava tulu arvel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Compensation paid to rail transport undertakings for the provision of public utility transport services shall cover at least the costs incurred in the provision of public utility transport services, including fees for the use of railway infrastructures which the rail transport undertaking cannot cover out of the income received from the provision of such services. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Uuml;hiskondlikku veoteenust osutaval raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjal on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud raudteeinfrastruktuuri kasutamise eelistus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Rail transport undertakings which provide public utility transport services shall be given priority in the use of railway infrastructures provided for in subsection 24 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeamet teavitab raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tjat &uuml;hiskondliku veoteenuse kasutamise vajadusest arvestusega, et &uuml;hiskondliku veoteenuse osutamise vajadus on teada l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>The Railway Administration shall notify railway infrastructure managers of the needs for public utility transport services such that the needs for the provision of public utility transport services are known upon distribution of capacity. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeregistrid </eesti>
<inglise>Railway Registers </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteede register </eesti>
<inglise>Register of railways </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteede register on riiklik register, kus registreeritakse avalikuks kasutamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud raudteed ja teised raudteed, sealhulgas depooteed. (2) Raudteede register asutatakse andmekogude seaduses (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) "Register of railways" means a state register for the registration of railways designated for public use and other railways, including depot sidings. (2) The register of railways shall be established pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Databases Act (RT I 1997, 28, 423; 1998, 36/37, 552; 1999, 10, 155; 2000, 50, 317; 57, 373; 92, 597; 2001, 7, 17; 2001, 17, 77), isikuandmete kaitse seaduse (RT I 1996, 48, 944; 1998, 59, 941; 111, 1833; 2000, 50, 317; 92, 597; 104, 685). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteede registri vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on Teede- ja Sideministeerium ning volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on Raudteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Ministry of Transport and Communications shall be the chief processor of the register of railways, and the Railway Administration shall be the authorised processor of the register of railways. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeveeremi register </eesti>
<inglise>Register of rail vehicles </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeveeremi register on riiklik register, kus registreeritakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud raudteeveerem. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) "Register of rail vehicles" means a state register for the registration of rail vehicles specified in subsection 5 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eestis esmakordselt kasutusele v&otilde;etavad raudteeveeremi t&uuml;&uuml;bid ja mudelid kuuluvad enne registrisse kandmist kohustuslikule kontrollimisele ja katsetusele, kinnitamaks nende vastavust raudteeveeremile kehtestatud n&otilde;uetele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Types and models of rail vehicles introduced in Estonia for the first time are subject to mandatory examination and testing prior to their entry into the register, in order to verify their compliance with the requirements established for rail vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeveeremi register asutatakse andmekogude seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The register of rail vehicles shall be established pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Databases Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raudteeveeremi registri vastutav t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on Teede- ja Sideministeerium ning volitatud t&ouml;&ouml;tleja on Raudteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Ministry of Transport and Communications shall be the chief processor of the register of rail vehicles, and the Railway Administration shall be the authorised processor of the register of rail vehicles. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteestatistika </eesti>
<inglise>Railway statistics </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeliikluse seisundi ning selles toimuvate muutuste hindamise eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;ib Raudteeamet riikliku statistika seaduse (RT I 1997, 51, 822) kohaselt korraldada statistilisi vaatlusi Vabariigi Valitsuse kinnitatud riiklike statistiliste vaatluste loetelu alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>In order to assess the state of railway traffic and changes therein, the Railway Administration may conduct statistical surveys pursuant to the Official Statistics Act (RT I 1997, 51, 822; 2000, 47, 289) and on the basis of the list of state statistical surveys approved by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeamet </eesti>
<inglise>Railway Administration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esolevas seaduses ja sellest tulenevates &otilde;igusaktides raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjate tegevusele kehtestatud n&otilde;uete j&auml;rgimise &uuml;le teostab Raudteeamet. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Railway Administration shall exercise state supervision over adherence to the requirements established for the activities of railway undertakings in this Act and legislation arising therefrom. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeametit juhib peadirektor, kelle nimetab ametisse teede- ja sideminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Railway Administration shall be directed by the Director General appointed by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeameti p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of Railway Administration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeameti p&auml;devus riikliku j&auml;relevalve teostamisel ning riikliku sunni kohaldamisel on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Railway Administration exercising state supervision and applying enforcement powers of the state is competent to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud tegevuslubade andmine, andmisest keeldumine, kehtetuks tunnistamine v&otilde;i kehtivuse l&otilde;petamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) issue, refuse to issue, revoke or terminate operating licences provided for in this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ohutustunnistuste v&auml;ljaandmine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) issue safety certificates; </inglise>
<eesti>3) raudtee tehnokasutuseeskirjas kehtestatud n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise kontrollimine ja ettekirjutuste tegemine n&otilde;uete rikkumise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>3) verify compliance with the requirements established in the rules for technical use of railway; issue precepts in the case of violations of the requirements </inglise>
<eesti>(06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.03.2001 entered into force 01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </inglise>
<eesti>4) vedurijuhtide eksamineerimise korraldamine ja vedurijuhilubade v&auml;ljaandmine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) administer examinations to locomotive drivers, and issue locomotive driver's licences; </inglise>
<eesti>5) raudteeinfrastruktuuri ehituskava heakskiitmise otsustamine ja raudteeinfrastruktuuri-rajatistele ehitusj&auml;relevalve teostamine; </eesti>
<inglise>5) decide on the approval of construction plans of railway infrastructures, and to exercise construction supervision over railway infrastructure constructions; </inglise>
<eesti>6) veoeeskirjade ja tegevuseeskirjade ning nende muudatuste heakskiitmise, avaldamise ja k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise otsustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>6) decide on the approval, publication and making available of transport rules and operating rules and amendments thereto; </inglise>
<eesti>(06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </eesti>
<inglise>(06.03.2001 entered into force 01.05.2001 - RT I 2001, 31, 170) </inglise>
<eesti>7) raudteeveo-ettev&otilde;tjaga &uuml;hiskondlike veoteenuste osutamiseks vastava lepingu s&otilde;lmimine; </eesti>
<inglise>7) enter into corresponding contracts with rail transport undertakings for the provision of public utility transport services; </inglise>
<eesti>8) kaebuste lahendamine raudteeinfrastruktuuri-ettev&otilde;tja poolt l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;imeosa eraldamata j&auml;tmise v&otilde;i diskrimineerivatel tingimustel eraldamise v&otilde;i vaba l&auml;bilaskev&otilde;ime jaotamata j&auml;tmise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>8) settle complaints if a railway infrastructure manager fails to allocate capacity or allocates capacity under discriminatory conditions, or fails to distribute free capacity; </inglise>
<eesti>9) raudteede registri ja raudteeveeremi registri pidamine ning nimetatud registrites sisalduvate andmete t&ouml;&ouml;tlemine Teede- ja Sideministeeriumi tellimisel; </eesti>
<inglise>9) maintain the register of railways and the register of rail vehicles, and process data contained therein on the order of the Ministry of Transport and Communications; </inglise>
<eesti>10) riiklike statistiliste vaatluste korraldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>10) conduct state statistical surveys; </inglise>
<eesti>11) rahvusvahelistest lepingutest tulenevate raudteega seonduvate Eesti Vabariigi kohustuste t&auml;itmise tagamine ja vajaduse korral Eesti Vabariigi esindamine rahvusvahelistes raudteeorganisatsioonides; </eesti>
<inglise>11) ensure compliance with the obligations of the Republic of Estonia related to railways arising from international agreements, and, if necessary, represent the Republic of Estonia in international railway organisations; </inglise>
<eesti>12) raudtee&otilde;nnetuste asjaolude v&auml;ljaselgitamise korraldamine; </eesti>
<inglise>12) organise the ascertainment of facts relating to railway accidents; </inglise>
<eesti>13) k&auml;esolevas seaduses etten&auml;htud juhtudel teadaannete avaldamine Riigi Teataja Lisas; </eesti>
<inglise>13) publish notices in the Riigi Teataja Lisa in the cases prescribed in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>14) muude seadustest tulenevate &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmine. </eesti>
<inglise>14) perform other duties arising from law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud p&auml;devuse piires v&otilde;ib Raudteeameti peadirektor anda v&auml;lja k&auml;skkirju, teha ettekirjutusi ja otsuseid ning volitada Raudteeameti ametnikke nende riikliku j&auml;relevalve p&auml;devuses tegema konkreetsete &uuml;ksikjuhtude kohta ettekirjutusi ja otsuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Within the limits of competence specified in subsection (1) of this section, the Director General of the Railway Administration may issue directives and precepts, make decisions and authorise the officials of the Railway Administration to issue precepts and make decisions concerning specific individual cases within the limits of their competence in state supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri ja raudteeveeremi tehnilise j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks vajalike toimingute tegemise ja vedurijuhtide eksamineerimise v&otilde;ib Raudteeamet teede- ja sideministri kehtestatud korras lepingu alusel edasi anda teistele isikutele. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Performance of acts necessary for exercising technical supervision over railway infrastructures and rail vehicles, and administration of examinations to locomotive drivers may be transferred to other persons by the Railway Administration on the basis of an agreement, and pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Transport and Communications. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud toimingute teostamise kulud tasub raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>Railway undertakings shall pay the costs related to the performance of such acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku j&auml;relevalve teostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Exercise of state supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudtee-ettev&otilde;tjad ja nende t&ouml;&ouml;tajad on kohustatud Raudteeametile ja teistele riikliku j&auml;relevalve asutustele andma t&otilde;est ja t&auml;ielikku teavet, mis on vajalik riikliku j&auml;relevalve &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Railway undertakings and the employees thereof are required to provide the Railway Administration and other state supervisory agencies with correct and complete information necessary for the performance of the duties of state supervision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riikliku j&auml;relevalve asutuste esindajatel on &otilde;igus vabaks juurdep&auml;&auml;suks j&auml;relevalveobjektiks olevale raudteeinfrastruktuurile ja raudteeveeremile ning raudtee-ettev&otilde;tja esindaja juuresolekul kaubale ja dokumentidele. (3) Raudteeametil on haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamise ja haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asja arutamise ning halduskaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramise &otilde;igus haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496) etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Representatives of state supervisory agencies have the right of free access to railway infrastructures and rail vehicles under supervision, and, in the presence of a representative of the railway undertaking, to the goods and documentation. (3) The Railway Administration has the right to prepare reports of administrative offences, hear administrative offence matters and impose administrative punishments pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 58, 608; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301; 49, 305; 51, 321; 54, 351; 54, 346; 54, 348; 54, 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544; 86, 548; 95, 609; 95, 613; 2001, 21, 115; 21, 116; 89, 578). </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus seaduse rikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for violation of law </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus seaduse rikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for violation of law </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i sellest tulenevate &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise eest kohaldatakse distsiplinaar-, haldus-, tsiviil- v&otilde;i kriminaalvastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary, administrative, civil or criminal liability shall be imposed for violation of this Act or legislation arising therefrom. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Seniste tegevuslubade kehtivus </eesti>
<inglise>Validity of current operating licences </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist raudteetranspordi korraldamiseks v&auml;ljaantud tegevusload j&auml;&auml;vad kehtima tegevusloas m&auml;rgitud t&auml;htajaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Operating licences issued for the organisation of rail transport before the entry into force of this Act shall remain valid for the term set out in the operating licence. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui tegevusloa t&auml;htaeg l&otilde;peb enne 2000. aasta 1. jaanuari, on nimetatud t&auml;htajani &otilde;igus saada tegevusluba ilma k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 9 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele vastavust kontrollimata. </eesti>
<inglise>If the term of validity of an operating licence expires before 1 January 2000, a new operating licence may be obtained up to the specified date without verification of compliance with the requirements provided for in subsection 9 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raudteeohutuse ja raudteeliikluse juhtimise eest vastutavad isikud ning raudteeveeremit juhtima &otilde;igustatud isikud v&otilde;ivad oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid t&auml;ita, omamata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 18 ja 19 etten&auml;htud kvalifikatsioonitunnistust ja vedurijuhiluba kuni 2000. aasta 1. jaanuarini. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons responsible for railway safety or railway traffic control and persons who have the right to drive rail vehicles may perform their duties until 1 January 2000 without a qualification certificate and locomotive driver's licence prescribed in &sect;&sect; 18 and 19 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteede m&auml;&auml;ramine avalikuks kasutamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>Designation of railways for public use </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisel loetakse AS Eesti Raudtee ja Edelaraudtee AS raudteed m&auml;&auml;ratuks avalikuks kasutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the entry into force of this Act, the railways of AS Eesti Raudtee and Edelaraudtee AS are deemed to be designated for public use. </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud raudteede loetelus muudatuste tegemine ja sealt v&auml;lja arvamine toimub k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 7 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Amendments to and exclusion from the list of these railways shall be effected pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 7 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri ehitiste arvelev&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of railway infrastructure structures </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeinfrastruktuuri ehitised, mis kuuluvad registreerimisele ehitiste kohta k&auml;ivates registrites, kantakse nendesse registritesse ehitiste valdaja taotlusel. </eesti>
<inglise>Railway infrastructure structures which are subject to registration in registers concerning structures shall be entered in such registers at the request of the possessors of the structures. </inglise>
<eesti>Registrisse kandmiseks vajalikud dokumendid koostatakse taotleja kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>Documents necessary for entry in a register shall be prepared at the expense of the applicant. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteemaa kasutamise erisused </eesti>
<inglise>Specifications concerning use of railway ground area </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Raudteeinfrastruktuuri hoonete ja rajatiste aluse ja nende teenindamiseks vajaliku maa (raudteemaa) riigi omandisse j&auml;tmise otsustab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Retention of land under railway infrastructure buildings or constructions, and land necessary for servicing such buildings and constructions (railway ground area) in state ownership shall be decided by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigi omandisse j&auml;etud raudteemaale seatakse hoonestus&otilde;igus raudteeinfrastruktuuri hoonete ja rajatiste omaniku kasuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Rights of superficies in the railway ground areas retained in state ownership shall be constituted for the benefit of the owners of railway infrastructure buildings or constructions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Raudteemaa, mida ei ole j&auml;etud riigi omandisse, ostuees&otilde;igusega erastamine toimub maareformiseaduses (RT 1991, 34, 426; RT I 1996, 41, 796; 1997, 13, 210; 37/38, 570; 81, 1363; 93, 1556; 1998, 12, 153; 103, 1698; 1999, 25, 366; 27, 390) s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Railway ground areas which are not retained in state ownership shall be privatised with the right of pre-emption on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Land Reform Act (RT 1991, 34, 426; RT I 2000, 70, 441; 88, 576; 2001, 31, 171). </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kuni k&auml;esolevas paragrahvis s&auml;testatud korras raudteemaa kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramiseni m&auml;&auml;rab raudtee&uuml;letuskoha piiri ning paigaldab sinna liikluskorraldusvahendid ja tagab raudtee&uuml;letuskoha korrashoiu ning liiklusohutuse raudteeinfrastruktuuriettev&otilde;tja tehnokasutuseeskirjas s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Until the determination of railway ground areas pursuant to the procedure provided for in this section, railway infrastructure managers shall determine the boundaries of railway crossings, install traffic control devices thereto and ensure the maintenance of and traffic safety on such railway crossings on the bases of and pursuant to the procedure provided for in the rules for technical use. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Raudteeseaduse kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Repeal of Railways Act </inglise>
<eesti>Tunnistada kehtetuks raudteeseadus (RT I 1995, 5, 41; 1998, 2, 45). </eesti>
<inglise>The Railways Act (RT I 1995, 5, 41; 1998, 2, 45) is repealed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse j&otilde;ustumine </eesti>
<inglise>Entry into force of Act This Act enters into force 1 May 1999. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esolev seadus j&otilde;ustub 1999. aasta 1. mail. </eesti>
